 orientation of\nimpurity bonds, but antiferromagnetically parallel to it, which results in a\nfan-like XY ground state. Second, we consider the case when the impurity bonds\nare randomly distributed on the three-dimensional host lattice according to a\nPoisson process. We show the phenomenon of spiral order by disorder with an\nordering wave vector proportional to the impurity concentration. The analytical\npredictions are confirmed by Monte Carlo simulations and are relevant for\nmagnetic materials such as YBaCuFeO_5.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Oct 2016 23:02:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 19 Oct 2016 14:59:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 9 Dec 2019 08:47:32 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 18 Dec 2019 16:18:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-18"}
