n the\nelectronic structure of Fe3+O6-compounds, we constrain the spin-pairing energy\nof Fe3+ in an octahedral field to ~ 20000-23000 cm-1. This implies that\noctahedrally-coordinated Fe3+ in bridgmanite is low spin at P > ~ 40 GPa.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Oct 2016 15:34:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-05"}
